TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Simulation Model of Capital Budgeting Under Uncertainty
AU  - Salazar, Rodolfo C.
AU  - Sen, Subrata K.
Y1  - 1968/12/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.4.B161
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.4.B161
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-161
EP  - B-179
VL  - 15
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper describes a simulation model of capital budgeting under uncertainty. It analyzes the effects of two types of uncertainty which influence the cash flows of the potential investment projects. Techniques of simulation and stochastic linear programming (using Weingartner's Basic Horizon model of capital budgeting) are employed to compute the expected return (with an associated measure of the risk involved) of different portfolios of projects. The manager can then select the portfolio which is closest to his personal risk-return preference. The model provides a practical guide to management in the entire process of project search, portfolio generation, and portfolio evaluation which characterizes the capital budgeting decision.
AB  - This paper describes a simulation model of capital budgeting under uncertainty. It analyzes the effects of two types of uncertainty which influence the cash flows of the potential investment projects. Techniques of simulation and stochastic linear programming (using Weingartner's Basic Horizon model of capital budgeting) are employed to compute the expected return (with an associated measure of the risk involved) of different portfolios of projects. The manager can then select the portfolio which is closest to his personal risk-return preference. The model provides a practical guide to management in the entire process of project search, portfolio generation, and portfolio evaluation which characterizes the capital budgeting decision.
